I hate TD games. They're passive, they're boring and they're a dime a dozen. But this is different! Instead of watching the fighting, you're actually a participant!  That makes all the difference in the world! It really breaths life into one of the most tired genres in mobile gaming. My only gripe, is that the graphics could use a little polish.

The only problem I have is that coop never finds a match for me.  Does anyone else have this problem?   The single player makes it completely worth the money though and I highly recommend this game to anyone.

When it works.......its fun.  Ive encountered a few glitches that are rather aggravating.  First, and most trivial, is that the games splash screen is only half rendered.  The right side of my screen is just a hodge podge of thumbnails from various menus and interfaces throughout the game.  Not that big of an issue.  The most irritating glitch is that the game locks and force closes.  It never occurs while playing, only after completing a stage and at the point I would receive my hard earned rewards.  Thats the most irritating one.  I've invested about 7 hours of play time into the game and the last bug has happened no less than 6 times.  Crystals arent easy to come by therefore I really want the one i would receive for my hard fought victory............."force close, no loot for you".  Grrr.  Im on a samsung galaxy tab 2.  If not for this last bug, its quite fun and $2 well spent.

This game took the best bits of Dynasty Warriors and the Defense games and put them all in one seamless package. You have direct participation in combat while managing the defenses of the castle. The game is pretty unforgiving at the later levels though, and properly building and adapting to the enemies that attack is one of the game's highlights. It's pretty good and there is enough selection of heroes to keep the game fresh. However, it still has room for improvement. A minimap or an indicator of where the enemies are would really help players, also the reticule for ranged heroes needs to be more prominent.

A tower defense and 3rd person fighting game all in one. Both elements executed exceptionally well. You will slash down the forces of evil darkness marching on your castle with your chosen hero while managing your castle defenses and various classes of warrior who will help you on the battle field. Graphics are at the top of their game for mobile devices which are not too far behind the latest consoles these days and controls are shockingly responsive for mobile as well. This game can get extremely hectic at times. You will get so caught up in the slashing-slashing-slashing, you will become distracted and may forget to manage your castle and soldiers. And at other times you will get so caught up in micro managing your castle and battlefield forces that you may leave your hero wide open to attack. This is the true challenge of this game. Finding the perfect balance between these two components amidst all the madness. In the end, it's the kind of hecticness you won't mind because it is all done so well and just plain FUN!
